&lt;p&gt;Job title – Consultant Midwife Midwifery Led Practice&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Area of Work - Core&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Employer - Lewisham and Greenwich NHS Trust&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Department - Maternity&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pay Band - 8B Agenda for change (Increments include higher cost of living allowance)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Location – University Hospital Lewisham - Inner London&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job type – Full time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date – 22.11.20&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Have you got at least 5 years post registration experience? Do you feel ready for a new challenge? This is an exciting opportunity for a Consultant Midwife to develop personally and professionally. The successfully candidate will work closely with the consultant midwife at Queen Elizabeth Hospital Woolwich.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Linking in to the ‘Better Births’ Agenda, this post will provide a unique opportunity for personal, professional, service and academic development individual in the role of Consultant Midwife.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To fulfil this varied role, you will need a flexible approach, an ability to ‘think outside the box’ and a willingness to not only embrace but lead on system wide changes in practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full time role that will require some weekend and out of hours working. It will be based at the Queen Elizabeth site but will have a cross site remit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Leading by example is crucial in collaborative working within the multidisciplinary team to maintain the Trusts Maternity philosophy of care. We are very proud of the Maternity Services that we provide across our sites and are looking for an influential midwife to support and encourage our philosophy of care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please read the Personal and Job specifications carefully. You should provide evidence in your application of the qualities required and why you would be an asset to this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to participate in a table top exercise as part of the Interview.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Short listing to be held: W/C 23.11.20&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview dates: W/C 30.11.20 (TBC)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information on this post please contact: Linda Machakaire on linda.machakaire@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
